    ('ANTH-E 260', 'CULTURE, HEALTH AND ILLNESS', '13031', 'Closed', 'Tu Tuesday 3:10 PM–4:00 PM', 'SB 231', 'George Armstrong', 0, 'Discussion', 'Lecture', '3', 'ERNIE PYLE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Across the world, ideas about and experiences of health, "dis-ease," and medicine are profoundly shaped by culture. Introduction to cross-cultural approaches to understanding health and illness, covering topics such as ethnomedicine, ritual healing, gender and health, and international development and global health.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
