COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 206', 'CLASSICAL ART AND ARCHAEOLOGY', '29739', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'JH A100', 'Lindsey Mazurek, Bryant Raisch', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BIOLOGY BUILDING', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Survey of the art and archaeology of Classical lands from the Minoan-Mycenaean Age through classical Greece and Rome. Emphasis upon the contributions of archeology to our understanding of classical cultural.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture
Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 207', 'INTRODUCTION TO CONTEMPORARY ART AND ITS DISCONTENTS, 1960 TO THE PRESENT', '8771', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'FA 102', 'Faye Gleisser', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'FINE ARTS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Provides a chronological overview of contemporary art (from 1960) with a focus on the social and political engagements that have informed artistic developments in recent decades. Examines the qualities that have made particular genres and artistic practices significant to art history; how globalization, tourism, technology, current world conflicts, and social media have shaped artistic production, art criticism, and the art market today.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Diversity in U.S.'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 224', 'THE GOTHIC CATHEDRAL', '29554', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'SE 140', 'Diane Reilly', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SWAIN EAST', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Studies the development of the Gothic cathedral, the most important cultural institution and innovating force in Europe in the development of architecture, visual arts, education and music. Examines trends in European architecture, sculpture and painting in the twelfth through fifteenth centuries, and the connections between the visual arts and politics, theology, music and religious practice.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 231', 'THE AGE OF GIANTS: ART IN THE TIME OF LEONARDO AND MICHELANGELO', '13517', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:35 AM–12:50 PM', 'WH 120', 'Giles Knox', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WOODBURN HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Italian painting and sculpture in the time of Leonardo da Vinci (1452-1519) and Michelangelo Buonarroti (1475-1564), whose accomplishments represent what S.J. Freedberg has called the "most extraordinary intersection of genius art history has known". Besides an overview of Italian High Renaissance art, major topics to be addressed include the rivalry between Leonardo and Michelangelo, Leonardo''s notebooks, and the reception of both artists'' works in later centuries.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture
Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 262', 'INTRODUCTION TO JAPANESE ART AND CULTURE', '29555', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'WH 101', 'Mycah Braxton', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WOODBURN HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Traces the transformation of painting and other artistic media, including ceramics, sculpture, scroll painting, and screens, through the epochs of Japanese art history. Emphasizes major moments of change, placing the visual arts in the context of international contact and the political and social order of Japan.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 280', 'THE ART OF THE COMIC STRIP', '29556', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 5:30 PM–6:45 PM', 'SW 007', 'Andrei Molotiu', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SWAIN WEST', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Surveys the formal and social history of the comic strip in America from its beginning in the mid 1800s to the present. Examines how the format created narrative challenges and conventions unique to comic strips and distinct from comic books as it surveys magazine comic strip humor, the newspaper comic strip and comic supplement, the continuity adventure strip, and postwar minimalist newspaper strips, to current comic strips and webcomics.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 281', 'INTRODUCTION TO ISLAMIC ART AND VISUAL CULTURE', '12896', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'TV 226', 'Maria Domene-Danes', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'RADIO-TV', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Survey of the spectacular art, architecture and visual culture of the Islamic world, from its beginnings in the seventh century through to the recent past.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 333', 'FROM VAN EYCK TO VERMEER', '32584', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'TV 226', 'Bret Rothstein', 16, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'RADIO-TV', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Survey of major artists and themes in Netherlandish painting from the 15th to the 17th century.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 342', '20TH CENTURY ART', '29557', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'LH 130', 'Jeffrey Saletnik', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'LINDLEY HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A survey of major artists, styles, and movements in painting and sculpture from 1900 to the present in Europe and the United States. Topics include Expressionism, Cubism, Futurism, Dada, Surrealism, and Abstraction.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 343', 'HISTORY OF 20TH CENTURY PHOTOGRPAHY', '31082', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'JH 001', 'Maria Domene-Danes', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BIOLOGY BUILDING', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Surveys twentieth century photography as a medium of art and communication. Considers portraiture, landscape, still life, the nude, conceptual photography, the social documentary tradition, the magazine picture story, fashion, advertising and war photography. Examines the impact of postmodern theories on photographic practice and the understanding of photography.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 345', 'AMERICAN ART TO 1913', '14841', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'LI 026', 'Melody Deusner', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WELLS LIBRARY', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'American architecture, sculpture, painting, photography, and graphics from seventeenth century to the Armory Show of 1913.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 400', 'SENIOR SEMINAR', '7222', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'SB 220', 'Faye Gleisser', 0, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'STUDENT BUILDING (FRANCES MORG', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Intensive examination of selected topics in art history. Open only to art history majors or with consent of instructor.', ARRAY['COLL INTENSIVE WRITING SECTIONS'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 410', 'TOPICS IN ANCIENT ART', '29688', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'SB 220', 'Lindsey Mazurek', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'STUDENT BUILDING (FRANCES MORG', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Special topics in the history and study of ancient and Classical art.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 410', 'TOPICS IN ANCIENT ART', '29687', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'LH 125', 'Nicholas Blackwell', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'STUDENT BUILDING (FRANCES MORG', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Special topics in the history and study of ancient and Classical art.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 446', 'AMERICAN ART, 1865-1945', '29560', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'TV 245', 'Melody Deusner', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'RADIO-TV', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'History of art in the United States from the end of the Civil War to the end of World War II.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL INTENSIVE WRITING SECTIONS'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 487', 'CARIBBEAN AND LATIN AMERICAN ART: EMPIRE, IDENTITY, AND SOCIETY', '33577', 'Class Status', 'M Monday 2:20 PM–4:50 PM', 'FX 150', 'Barbaro Martinez-Ruiz', 15, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'MCCALLA', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Focuses on the emergence of an African aesthetic and its conceptual principles, from the first stirrings in the 16th century of Africans dislocated through the slave trade to the early 20th century, when most African artistic and cultural expressions were fully developed and firmly rooted throughout the Americas.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 490', 'TOPICS IN ART HISTORY', '29561', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'BH 306', 'Mycah Braxton', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Topic varies with the instructor and year and will be listed in the Schedule of Classes.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 501', 'TOPICS IN ANCIENT ART', '29689', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'LH 125', 'Nicholas Blackwell', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'LINDLEY HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Special topics in the history and study of Ancient Art.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 501', 'TOPICS IN ANCIENT ART', '29690', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'SB 220', 'Lindsey Mazurek', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'LINDLEY HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Special topics in the history and study of Ancient Art.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 510', 'CRITICAL THEORIES AND METHODS IN ART HISTORY, CA 1900-PRESENT', '29562', 'Class Status', 'M Monday 3:10 PM–6:10 PM', 'PY 115', 'Bret Rothstein', 2, NULL, 'Colloquium', '3', 'PSYCHOLOGY', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course provides graduate students the opportunity to examine methodologies developed in Art History since its efflorescence as a modern discipline in the late 19th century. Readings, discussion, and individual research will help students develop an understanding of how critical theory has shaped art historical practice.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 558', 'AMERICAN ART, 1865-1945', '30231', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'TV 245', 'Melody Deusner', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'RADIO-TV', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'History of Art in the United States from the end of the Civil War to World War II.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 580', 'TOPICS IN ART HISTORY', '30232', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'BH 306', 'Mycah Braxton', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Special topics in the history and study of Art History in various centuries.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 587', 'CARIBBEAN AND LATIN AMERICAN ART: EMPIRE, IDENTITY, AND SOCIETY', '33578', 'Class Status', 'M Monday 2:20 PM–4:50 PM', 'FX 150', 'Barbaro Martinez-Ruiz', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'MCCALLA', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The class will focus on the emergence of an African aesthetic and its conceptual principles, from the first stirrings in the 16th century of Africans dislocated through the slave trade to the early 20th century, when most African artistic and cultural expressions were developed and rooted throughout the Americas.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ARTH-A 590', 'MUSEUM STUDIES', '14420', 'Class Status', 'W Wednesday 11:10 AM–2:10 PM', 'HD TBA', 'Allison Martino', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BLDG NOT ASSIGNED', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Course is designed to utilize the resources of the Indiana University Art Museum for academic research. Topics vary: cataloguing, technical examination, organizing exhibitions, etc.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
