    ('ASCS-Q 296', 'COLLEGE TO CAREER II: NAVIGATE YOUR ARTS AND SCIENCES EXPERIENCE', '6206', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:10 AM–10:00 AM', 'EP 214', 'Jed Junken', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '2', 'ERNIE PYLE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Explores the relationship between academic and extracurricular choices and life after graduation. Students assess their skills, develop a portfolio to highlight them, and create a plan to address gaps. Focuses on a paradigm of job searching that emphasizes research and highly customized, focused application materials.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) Career Readiness 1
